                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d886">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.6363 Manchuria/303: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-02T16:00:00+09:00"
                            >July 2, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 2—6:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>175. Department’s 81, June 12, 4 p.m., American oil claim. Informal and oral
                    representations made today and Consul at Mukden instructed to proceed in
                    accordance with Department’s 64, April 22, 2 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
